11/11/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Veselin Bliznakov honoured on Thursday (10 November) the soldiers who helped plan, organise and execute the so-called Phoenix operation to rebuild the infrastructure in areas devastated by floods this past summer. The army reportedly helped rebuild or repair 45 facilities and disinfected dozens of schools throughout the country. (Sega - 11/11/05; Novinite - 10/11/05) 
